  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0cm 5.75pt 0cm 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Paratis are a medium sized insectoid, having an
  exoskeleton with very few visible sensory organs. </p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Paratis are very passive in nature, although the=
y live
  lives as mostly individuals who do not interact with other Paratis often =
they
  are however social in nature in terms of cooperation to achieve similar
  goals. </p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Paratis are not trustworthy despite their seemingly =
placid
  nature, they are often plotting their own advancement through other means
  than force.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Paratis deep knowledge of missile systems and th=
eir
  delivery has culminated in the development of the Paratis Hammerhead.<span
  style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>A missile system allowing quick
  delivery of a large payload.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;
  </span>Because of the unique design the Paratis Hammerhead has a limited
  range compared to other missiles but makes up for this in raw firepower.<=
/p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Paratis often socially act out wars. This game i=
s a
  combination of competitive, social and training that many enjoy. This game
  can vary in level of brutality depending on the stakes but is also a form=
 of
  entertainment transmitted for leisure universally and their greatest hero=
es
  are often the best at the sport.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Paratis preferred weapon is the Missile and they=
 have
  a Balanced approach with Energy Research.<i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:=
normal'><o:p></o:p></i></p>
